</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
This species differs from all other species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Smicridea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Smicridea nigripennis" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Smicridea nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group due to the presence of a simple aedeagus, with only a sclerotized spine, and large rounded lobe in segment X (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.330" author="Flint, Jr OS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 61" refId="B26" refString="Flint, Jr OS, 1981. Studies of Neotropical Caddisflies, XXVIII: The Trichoptera of the Rio Limon Basin, Venezuela. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 330 (330): 1 - 61, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.330" title="Studies of Neotropical Caddisflies, XXVIII: The Trichoptera of the Rio Limon Basin, Venezuela." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.330" volume="330" year="1981">Flint 1981</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Smicridea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Smicridea (Smicridea) palifera" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palifera" subGenus="Smicridea">Smicridea (Smicridea) palifera</taxonomicName>
presents a wide distribution in Brazil, except in the south of the country (
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, APM" journalOrPublisher="PeerJ" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" publicationUrl="http://fauna.jbrj.gov.br/fauna/faunadobrasil/278" refId="B68" refString="Santos, APM, Dumas, LL, Henriques-Oliveira, AL, Souza, WRM, Camargos, LM, Calor, AR, Pes, AMO, 2022. Trichoptera in Catalogo Taxonomico da Fauna do Brasil. PNUD. http://fauna.jbrj.gov.br/fauna/faunadobrasil/278" title="Trichoptera in Catalogo Taxonomico da Fauna do Brasil. PNUD." url="http://fauna.jbrj.gov.br/fauna/faunadobrasil/278" year="2022">Santos et al. 2022</bibRefCitation>
). In the Northeast region it has been registered in four states (altitude range of 53 m and 814 m) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" author="Souza, WRM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 10" refId="B76" refString="Souza, WRM, Lima, LRC, Pes, AMO, Pinheiro, U, 2013a. Trichoptera (Insecta) from Pernambuco State, northeastern Brazil. Journal of Natural History 48 (45-46): 1 - 10, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" title="Trichoptera (Insecta) from Pernambuco State, northeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" volume="48" year="2013 a">Souza et al. 2013a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" author="Desiderio, GR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="151 - 171" refId="B20" refString="Desiderio, GR, Barcelos-Silva, P, Souza, WD, Pes, AM, Azevedo, CD, 2017. Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records. Zootaxa 422 (2): 151 - 171, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" title="Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" volume="422" year="2017">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Desidério">Desiderio</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/aen.12459" author="Desiderio, GR" journalOrPublisher="Austral Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="265 - 279" refId="B21" refString="Desiderio, GR, Razuri-Gonzales, E, Pes, AM, Hamada, N, 2020. Smicridea (Smicridea) nigripennis species group (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae) from Brazil: new species, new distributional records and an identification key. Austral Entomology 59 (2): 265 - 279, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/aen.12459" title="Smicridea (Smicridea) nigripennis species group (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae) from Brazil: new species, new distributional records and an identification key." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/aen.12459" volume="59" year="2020">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Desidério">Desiderio</normalizedToken>
et al. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). It was recorded in the Caatinga domain, Pernambuco state (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" author="Souza, WRM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 10" refId="B76" refString="Souza, WRM, Lima, LRC, Pes, AMO, Pinheiro, U, 2013a. Trichoptera (Insecta) from Pernambuco State, northeastern Brazil. Journal of Natural History 48 (45-46): 1 - 10, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" title="Trichoptera (Insecta) from Pernambuco State, northeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" volume="48" year="2013 a">Souza et al. 2013a</bibRefCitation>
) and later the Cerrado and Atlantic Forest domains (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" author="Desiderio, GR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="151 - 171" refId="B20" refString="Desiderio, GR, Barcelos-Silva, P, Souza, WD, Pes, AM, Azevedo, CD, 2017. Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records. Zootaxa 422 (2): 151 - 171, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" title="Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" volume="422" year="2017">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Desidério">Desiderio</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/aen.12459" author="Desiderio, GR" journalOrPublisher="Austral Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="265 - 279" refId="B21" refString="Desiderio, GR, Razuri-Gonzales, E, Pes, AM, Hamada, N, 2020. Smicridea (Smicridea) nigripennis species group (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae) from Brazil: new species, new distributional records and an identification key. Austral Entomology 59 (2): 265 - 279, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/aen.12459" title="Smicridea (Smicridea) nigripennis species group (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae) from Brazil: new species, new distributional records and an identification key." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/aen.12459" volume="59" year="2020">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Desidério">Desiderio</normalizedToken>
et al. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Brejo de Altitude</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
